-- reverse-string-crystal.cell: string reversal crystallization
-- Oracle: reverse it again, should get original back

вҠў reverse
  given text вүЎ "hello world"
  yield reversed

  вҲҙ Reverse the characters in В«textВ».
    "hello" вҶ’ "olleh"

вҠў verify-reverse
  given reverseвҶ’reversed
  given text вүЎ "hello world"
  yield roundtrip

  вҲҙ Reverse В«reverseвҶ’reversedВ» again.
    If the result equals В«textВ», the reversal is correct.
    Return the re-reversed string.

  вҠЁ roundtrip = "hello world"

вҠў crystallize
  given В§reverse
  given verify-reverseвҶ’roundtrip where roundtrip = "hello world"
  yield В§reverse', is-faithful

  вҲҙ Read В«В§reverseВ». It reverses a string character by character.
    Write a вҠў= expression that does the same thing.

вҠў verify-crystal
  given В§reverse'
  given crystallizeвҶ’is-faithful
  given reverseвҶ’reversed
  yield approved

  вҲҙ Does В«В§reverse'В» use only вҠў= primitives?

  вҠЁ if approved and crystallizeвҶ’is-faithful then В§reverse' may replace В§reverse
